The paper discusses automatic test-case generation techniques for discovering vulnerabilities in software systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The focus is on improving path coverage and discovering vulnerabilities, which are also relevant to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), programming languages (cs.PL), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper primarily deals with software testing and vulnerability discovery, cs.SE is the most likely category.
